        "text": "An important thing about threaded media is the space they can establish for **deliberating** in a community. So, affordance for **polling** and transparently **registering** points of view is part of this. \n> Apps vary a lot in with regard to polling or voting tools, and very few of them are very good at this - Loomio stands out. But other kinds of ‘community standing’ or ‘trust’ are sometimes tooled-up (specialised tools to support ‘contribution accounting’ are closer to this: see ‘specials’ below). \n"
